'''Halberds''', also referred to by players as '''hallies''', are long two-handed [[Weapons#Basic melee weapons|melee weapons]] with blades similar to [[axe]]s and handles made up of long poles. All halberds have a slow [[attack speed]] of 7 [[ticks]], the same as [[Two-handed sword|2h swords]], but they can hit opponents from a [[Attack range|range]] two squares away, as opposed to the usual one square distance of most melee weapons. In addition to sharing the attack speed, most halberds have similar strength and slash bonuses to their 2h sword counterparts, falling behind in strength bonus and accuracy while making up for this in increased range and defence bonuses. The exception to this is the white and black halberds, which have significantly lower strength bonuses which equal the steel halberd.

A player may only wield a [[dragon halberd]] once they have completed the [[Regicide]] quest and the [[crystal halberd]] can only be wielded after completion of the [[Western Provinces Diary#Hard|Hard Western Provinces Diary]]. The other halberds can be worn anytime, so long as you have the right [[Attack]] level (and with some the right [[Strength]] level) to wield them.

Halberds can be used in "[[safespot]]s", or locations where a player can hit a monster and not get hit back, for example across a gate or fence.

Halberds cannot be created with the [[Smithing]] skill.

